n scientific objective is to map and study the variations in lunar surface composition, as well as the location and abundance of lunar water.", "extract_html": "<p><b>Chandrayaan-2</b> is the second lunar exploration mission developed by ISRO after Chandrayaan-1. It consists of a lunar orbiter, the <i>Vikram</i> lunar lander, and the <i>Pragyan</i> rover, all of which were developed in India. The main scientific objective is to map and study the variations in lunar surface composition, as well as the location and abundance of lunar water.</p>"}
